-- Avod Jumps Most in 10 Weeks After Plan to View Strategic Options
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-02-23T10:06:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-23/avod-jumps-most-in-10-weeks-after-plan-to-view-strategic-options.html
Avod Kurutulmus Gida & Tarim
Urunleri Sanayi Ticaret AS (AVOD) , a producer of dried vegetables,
surged the most in 10 weeks in Istanbul, after hiring an adviser
to study options for possible strategic actions and domestic and
foreign borrowing.  Avod rose 8.7 percent to 3.11 liras at 11:59 a.m., in the
biggest increase since Dec. 13. Avod signed an investment
consultancy agreement with broker Endeks Turev Menkul Degerler
AS to assess borrowing options and strategic alternatives,
including partnerships, mergers and restructuring, it said in a
statement to the  Istanbul Stock Exchange  after the market closed
yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
